From: PS3 Custom Toolchain
Subject: [PATCH] cell64lv2: pin DWARF2_ADDR_SIZE to 8 (match ELF64 wrapper)

GCC's default for DWARF2_ADDR_SIZE is POINTER_SIZE/BITS_PER_UNIT.  Under
our default ILP32 hybrid ABI POINTER_SIZE is 32, so the default rule
yields DWARF2_ADDR_SIZE == 4.  Our output ELF wrapper is class ELF64
regardless of pointer width, so debug-info address fields must be 8
bytes to match the wrapper.  Without this override, the DWARF emitter
selects DW_OP_const4u for a thread-local DW_AT_location and routes
through TARGET_ASM_OUTPUT_DWARF_DTPREL with size==4, which emits

    .long sym@dtprel+0x8000

Binutils' PowerPC64 backend resolves the `@dtprel' suffix to a 64-bit
R_PPC64_DTPREL64 relocation, which does not fit in the 4-byte `.long'
slot, and the assembler fails with:

    Error: R_PPC64_DTPREL64 relocations do not fit in 4 bytes

Pinning DWARF2_ADDR_SIZE to 8 routes the same path through DW_OP_const8u
and an 8-byte (`.8byte') dtprel slot, which encodes a real DTPREL64 and
assembles cleanly.  DWARF address fields and relocation slots become 8
bytes because the wrapper is ELF64; the underlying EA values stay in
the 32-bit virtual range under the default ILP32 hybrid, only the
storage width grows to match the ELF class.

Precedent: MIPS sets DWARF2_ADDR_SIZE from FILE_HAS_64BIT_SYMBOLS rather
than POINTER_SIZE for exactly this reason.  GCC's mainline biarch x32
(x86) and aarch64-ilp32 do not face this question because both emit
class-32 ELF objects when their C pointer width is 32.  Our wrapper is
always class-64, so the conditional collapses to the constant 8.

The override is also correct for the -mlp64 multilib (POINTER_SIZE 64
already gives DWARF2_ADDR_SIZE 8 by the default rule, so 8 matches).

--- a/gcc/config/rs6000/cell64lv2.h
+++ b/gcc/config/rs6000/cell64lv2.h
@@ -409,6 +409,16 @@
 #undef  PREFERRED_DEBUGGING_TYPE
 #define PREFERRED_DEBUGGING_TYPE DWARF2_DEBUG
 
+/* The output ELF wrapper is always class ELF64, regardless of whether
+   the C ABI is the default ILP32 hybrid or the -mlp64 multilib opt-in.
+   DWARF address fields must mirror the ELF class, not the C pointer
+   width: under the default ILP32 hybrid POINTER_SIZE is 32 but the
+   ELF64 wrapper still stores 8-byte address fields.  This also keeps
+   TARGET_ASM_OUTPUT_DWARF_DTPREL on the 8-byte path for thread-local
+   DW_AT_location, where binutils only encodes R_PPC64_DTPREL64.  */
+#undef  DWARF2_ADDR_SIZE
+#define DWARF2_ADDR_SIZE 8
+
 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Function size / constant pool / EH encoding (shared with linux64).
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------- */
